<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-746] Other registered failing RunListeners cause NullPointerException in ConcurrentReporterManager, falsely report of &quot;No tests were executed!&quot;: </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-746</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A Custom Runner in JUnit can register their own RunListeners on the RunNotifier during execution. When these fail, junit removes them from the Listener chain and fires a &apos;internal&apos; Failure, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;RunNotifier.SafeNotifier:44&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;fireTestFailure(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Failure(Description.TEST_MECHANISM, e));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When a unknown Failure is fired with a &apos;unknown&apos; Description as compared to surefires pre created metadata registry, it fails with a NullPointerException and is removed by JUnit. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;No tests are found&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
